Comment: The thing with the Hound is that to complete his character arch he has to die Which sucks But it makes his character even stronger Building a character in a movie tv show or a video game that people care for isn t easy But with Sandor they did the best job I ve ever seen A character we were almost forced to hate and despise Bc of the side he was on But we spent more time with him throughout the show We saw who he truly was And we saw him become in some ways good This causes a deeper impact a deeper connection with the character Because a character arch like this is something most people can relate to Especially when he helps Sansa and Arya We place ourselves in the girl s shoes Bc we too have had teachers Sometimes we didn t always see what they were teaching us but eventually when we do we appreciate them That was Sandor to Arya and Sansa A teacher Whom they didn t realize had good intentions and truly wanted to help them But now they do see that side of him And so do we as an audience We ve related to him and now we care about him most of us do And the final act to truly make his character arch complete is death We ve all lost someone who was like a teacher to us Whether that be a grandparent a parent or a mentor to us We ve experienced loss We ve lost someone we ve cared for And how they ve built up Sandor so far is very similar We care about him we want the best for him But in the end we are gonna feel actual pain when he dies Bc it s gonna feel like we actually lost a friend or a mentor Thus Sandor is an incredible character with an even better character arch

Comment: Joe Blow You are correct And I think Jaime s arc is more compelling because it is bigger Sandor went from a grumpy b d who killed people out of cynicism to a grumpy b d who kills people out of a sense of purpose It s impressive for sure but not fundamentally transformative to his character He is who he always was merely with more just justifications for his actions Jaime has gone from utterly selfish with a tiny suppressed nugget of higher purpose to a man who lives for purpose only and has apparently discarded the last of his selfish persona Jaime is a fundamentally different person at the end of his arc Sandor s arc is within our grasps as normal people We could all live his arc ourselves if not killing people then something we do that is less bloody where we learn to let our better self out but are largely the same person It s a nice story Jaime s arc is epic It s beyond the grasp of normal people and is more like an arc rarely seen where someone gives up everything to be a missionary in the slums of Calcutta for example It s the complete abandonment of one safe life focused on self to an insecure life focused on others There are many character arcs in GOT where the characters end up better versions or worse versions but they mostly end up dead of themselves There is only one arc however where the person at the end has no resemblance to the person at the beginning Jaime is the only character who sits wholly unrecognizable entering Season from where they started in Season

something like this The coming war is going to be disastrous for everyone south of the wall As dragonglass and fire and valerian steel are used to kill the army of the dead the southern army will never be able to get ahead Limited manpower meaning a finite of fighters is juxtaposed against the army of the dead s ever increasing numbers as casualties mount And in spite of Jon Snow and company s heroics and Dany s remaining dragons the tide slowly inexorably turns against them Jon will be lost Dany will be lost Arya dead Jamie and Cersei dead The southern armies practically annihilated UNTIL when all seems lost we see the walking dead corpse of Hodor standing not far behind the Night King And at that moment when all seems lost and the Night King is about to receive the cup of victory and the eminent death of all mankind someone Arya Bronn shoots a weir wood arrow at the Night King All seems lost until Bran worgs into the walking dead corpse of Hodor and stabs him with the fallen arrow thereby destroying the Night King and all of his army Evil as we have known it has left the Kingdoms except the evil that lives in the hearts of men that will never go away so of course there will still be theiving and killing but mostly we ll enter into the most peaceful and prosperous times in history And who will be left Tyrion will rule as regent until Jon Snow and Dany s baby grows up with Bronn and Pod by his side And sure Tyrion will grumble that Yara s Iron Island people are still ravaging and the masters of Slaver s Bay are still slaving etc But he ll resign himself that this is the way of the world as it s been for thousands of years And even a just ruler a ruler who loves playing the game like himself can t expect to change things overnight So no need to fret and worry too much He has a kingdom to run in the stead of Jon Dany s baby And there s wine to be drunk And whores to fuck And stories to tell with his friends Bronn and Pod And far away from King s Landing we see lady knight Brienne and former wildling Tormond start a fledgling and frustrating and funny relationship We see Sansa as lady of Winterfell and Queen if the North We see Yara as Queen of the Iron Islands We see young lady Mormont as Queen of Bear Island And we see Sandor Cleghane finally living in peace never having to pick up his sword again That s how I see it

Comment: I bought the odyssey I m returning it for several reasons first is the feels low quality the fact it s lighter is a plus but I feel like I will break it easily and while that might not be the case it just feels that way second is the fitment The fit much better swapping my rifts vr cover to it and it did help with clarity being closer to lens but it s just not comfortable at least not for me The nose piece digs into you and to get it secure it s instant headache from having to have it tight third sweet spot ipd sde goodrays The sweet spot is def better on the rift it s very small on the and while everyone is talking about sde being virtual gone that s true however because of the lenses they you you can see the lenses rings when you get the godrays and trust me when I say this you notice those rings a lot and they bothered me more than the sde on the rift the ipd sucks too if you have anything smaller than I have So the only going to means for me anyways I can only get one eye really centered Fourth is clarity Everyone is saying how clear it is but I tried every SS combo I could try and I just could not get as sharp of a image as the rift The just feels blurry Forget everyone sugar coating it saying softer softer blurry in VR

Comment: I finally got my Odyssey plus If it wasn t for your recommendation in another video to give it some time I might have returned it by now The two immediate things I found about it compared with my original Odyssey it s more comfortable I was initially concerned about all the extra space beneath the nose area and light leak but that really turned into a non issue when you re in VR However it really is not as sharp as the original Odyssey It appears to me that things you see in the distance is more blurry That really annoyed me at first but then I kept adjusting it and found that if I lower the headset as low as I could on the back of my head things get better After using it now for several hours of gaming it s really growing on me I am experiencing one issue with it in that every once in a while it picks up very loud noises in the speakers and I don t know why Ultimately the only way I got it to stop was a reboot I ll have to spend some time looking into that It doesn t happen with my original Odyssey so I m wondering about if it has something to do with the builtin Bluetooth I have to say the comfort level is greatly improved and so that really makes much of the difference as to why I m liking this new unit
